to avoid using $ in test class names, but it seems inner classes do compile with it. It's also about public top-level classes and having the right package structure, possibly outside the library. I’m planning to implement the `ExtensionLoaderTest` class with some specific tests. I need to ensure robust coverage for all possible call sites, including various constructor scenarios.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding class access and constructors**\\n\\nI’m figuring out the implications of declaring a class as public static. If the class is public, then the constructors should also be public, right? I believe that the default constructor also has the same access level as the class itself. There won't be an issue with `getDeclaredConstructor`. I need to ensure the extension interface uses `getName`, and I'm considering potential duplicate key conflicts when loading. But actually, it seems that's not a concern, so maybe I don’t need `ExtensionLoader.asMap` to be unmodifiable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0wb0B3pw86uXsxhsUiPtZMIp|fc_0aebf92aa2c15696016a000181d6bc81909c07cd43f722b196", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.wiremock/wiremock/3.13.1/src/test/java/org_wiremock/wiremock/ExtensionLoaderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_wiremock.wiremock;\n\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.extension.Extension;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.extension.ExtensionLoader;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ExtensionLoaderTest {\n    @Test\n    void loadsExtensionByClassName() {\n        Map<String, Extension> extensions = ExtensionLoader.load(ByClassNameExtension.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(extensions)\n                .containsOnlyKeys(\"extension-loader-by-class-name\");\n        assertThat(extensions.get(\"extension-loader-by-class-name\"))\n                .isInstanceOf(ByClassNameExtension.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsExtensionByClassLiteral() {\n        Map<String, Extension> extensions = ExtensionLoader.load(ByClassLiteralExtension.class);\n\n        assertThat(extensions)\n                .containsOnlyKeys(\"extension-loader-by-class-literal\");\n        assertThat(extensions.get(\"extension-loader-by-class-literal\"))\n                .isInstanceOf(ByClassLiteralExtension.class);\n    }\n\n    public static class ByClassNameExtension implements Extension {\n        @Override\n        public String getName() {\n            return \"extension-loader-by-class-name\";\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ByClassLiteralExtension implements Extension {\n        @Override\n        public String getName() {\n            return \"extension-loader-by-class-literal\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 361, "output": 961, "cacheRead": 10240, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 11562, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778385272879, "responseId": "resp_0aebf92aa2c15696016a0001796a04819089ee17ca7c38911e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_0wb0B3pw86uXsxhsUiPtZMIp|fc_0aebf92aa2c15696016a000181d6bc81909c07cd43f722b196", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1683 bytes to tests/src/org.wiremock/wiremock/3.13.1/src/test/java/org_wiremock/wiremock/ExtensionLoaderTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778385283435}]}
